I freely admit that when I created my erudite paladin I knew nothing about the game, therefore my base stats are garbage. I assumed that a paladin would need good intelligence ( I know, I Know..... RTFM) working on the basis that a 'Knight of Honour' would be highly educated. That and the fact I thought Erudites looked cool led to the creation of Queig.<br>
<br>
I also admit that many times I have been sorely tempted to throw in the towel and re-roll him, and have played every other class on other servers (although not to particularly high lvls) and I keep coming back to my pally.<br>
<br>
And if anyone gives me a hard time about being an Erudite I just read out the stats on my SotSS and grin.<br>
<br>
When it comes down to it you either take to a class, and adopt it so to speak, or you try another until you do. Never play a class because of what he/she can do. Play it because you enjoy it. <p><p><img border="0" src="http://www.queig.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/qsig2.gif"></p>

